  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and grate or chop finely</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>coriander stems</strong> from their <strong>leaves</strong> and chop the <strong>stems</strong> and the <strong>leaves</strong> finely, keeping them separate&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>beef mince</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>coriander stems</strong>,<strong> fish sauce</strong> and half the <strong>red curry paste</strong> in a mixing bowl</p>\r\n<p>Mix thoroughly until everything is fully combined (use clean hands!)</p>\r\n<p>Divide the mixture into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> and shape into balls</p>\r\n<p>Refrigerate until later&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: chilling the meatballs helps them hold their shape when cooking&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> Thai rice noodles</strong> to a pot of <strong>salted</strong> <strong>boiled water</strong> (enough to cover them) on a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Boil for 4-6 min, or until they're cooked through but with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, drain and rinse them briefly under cold water, shaking off the excess water before returning them to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478__step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478__step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478__step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478__step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478__step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Combine the<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong>, <strong>lime juice</strong> and remaining<strong> red curry paste</strong> and mix together thoroughly - this is your <strong>Thai dressing</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop or crush the<strong> roasted peanuts</strong> coarsely</p>\r\n<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/478_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil&nbsp;</strong>over a high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chilled meatballs</strong> and cook them for 4 min, or until they've browned&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: use tongs to turn them regularly for even cooking</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
